_emoticon_aria_closing_parenthesis.comme: words to be read aloud by a screen reader for the ')' character
_emoticon_aria_combined_title.comment: Text read by screen reader software describing an emoticon. {{name}} is the full name of the emoticon which is translated, {{shortName}} is the short name of the emoticon, which is not translated. {{openingParenthesis}} is the name of the '(' character and {{closingParenthesis}} is the name of the ')' character. The shortcut for an emoticon is its shortname surrounded by parenthesis, and since this string is read by screen reading software, we want to ensure that the parentheses are spoken aloud
_emoticon_aria_opening_parenthesis.comme: words to be read aloud by a screen reader for the '(' character
_emoticon_combined_title.comment: Text used as the tooltip for an emoticon. {{name}} is the full name of the emoticon which is translated, {{shortName}} is the short name of the emoticon surrounded by parentheses, which is not translated
_emoticon_combined_skintone_title.commen: Text used as the tooltip for an emoticon. {{name}} is the full name of the emoticon which is translated, {{shortName}} is the short name of the emoticon surrounded by parentheses, which is not translated, {{skinTone}} is the skin tone of the emoticon.
_emoticon_name_with_skintone.comment: Used for accessibility - thumbs up with medium skin tone - {{name}} is the emoticon name and {{skinTone}} is the skin pigmentation
_emoticon_skintone_default.comment: The base yellow skin tone for default emoticons
_emoticon_skintone_medium_light.comment: Used for medium light skin tone
_emoticon_skintone_medium_dark.comment: Used for medium dark skin tone
